\f3\fs28 [see, *e.g.*,\\]\\[][#Coffman2014,Exley2019]
\f2\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28 , a tendency to update too much when faced with negative signals
\f2\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\fs28 [#Mobius2014]
\f2\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28 , be more easily swayed by the opinions of others
\f2\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\fs28 [#Born2019]
\f2\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  or exert more effort on low stakes tasks
\f2\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\fs28 [#Schlosser2019]
\f2\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  and those which do not yield obvious benefits
